heta_{1})$$ and $$z_{2} = r_{2}(\\cos \\theta_{2} + i \\sin \\theta_{2})$$\n;$$\\frac{z_{1}}{z_{2}} = \\frac{r_{1}}{r_{2}}(\\cos (\\theta_{1} - \\theta_{2}) + i \\sin (\\theta_{1} - \\theta_{2}))$$\n;$$|\\frac{z_{1}}{z_{2}}| = \\frac{r_{1}}{r_{2}} = \\frac{|z_{1}|}{|z_{2}|}$$\n;$$arg(\\frac{z_{1}}{z_{2}}) = \\theta_{1} - \\theta_{2} = arg z_{1} - arg z_{2}$$ ',17),(439,'Geometry of Complex Numbers in Trigonometric Form','F','(a) Unit of Complex Numbers: \n;A complex number with $$|z| = \\sqrt{x^2 + y^2} = 1$$: $$z = \\cos \\theta + i \\sin \\theta$$\n;\n;(b) Negative of $$z$$\n;$$z = r (\\cos \\theta + i \\sin \\theta)$$\n;$$- z = r (\\cos (\\theta \\pm \\pi) + i \\sin (\\theta \\pm \\pi))$$\n;$$arg(-z) = \\theta \\pm \\pi = arg(z) \\pm \\pi$$\n;\n;(c) Conjugate of $$z$$\n;$$z = r (\\cos \\theta + i \\sin \\theta)$$\n;$$z^* = r (\\cos (-\\theta) + i \\sin (-\\theta))$$\n;$$|z^*| = r = |z|$$\n;$$arg(z^*) = -\\theta = - arg(z)$$\n;\n;(d) Reciprocal of $$z$$\n;$$z = r (\\cos \\theta + i \\sin \\theta)$$\n;$$\\frac{1}{z} = \\frac{1}{r}(\\cos (-\\theta) + i \\sin (-\\theta))$$\n;$$|\\frac{1}{z}| = \\frac{1}{r} = \\frac{1}{|z|}$$ and $$arg(\\frac{1}{z}) = -\\theta = - arg(z)$$\n;\n;(e) $$kz$$\n;$$z = r (\\cos \\theta + i \\sin \\theta)$$\n;$$kz = kr (\\cos \\theta + i \\sin \\theta)$$\n;$$|kz| = kr = k|z|$$\n;$$arg(kz) = \\theta = arg(z)$$\n;\n;(f) $$iz$$\n;$$z = r (\\cos \\theta + i \\sin \\theta)$$\n;$$iz = r (\\cos (\\theta + \\pi/2) + i \\sin (\\theta + \\pi/2))$$\n;$$|iz| = r = |z|$$\n;$$arg(iz) = \\theta + \\pi/2 = arg(z) + \\pi/2$$',17),(440,'Algebra of Complex Numbers in Exponential Form','C','Let $$z_{1} = r_{1}e^{i \\theta_{1}}$$ and $$z_{2} = r_{2}e^{i \\theta_{2}}$$\n;\n;(1) $$z_{1}z_{2} = r_{1}e^{i \\theta_{1}} r_{2}e^{i \\theta_{2}} =  r_{1}r_{2}e^{i(\\theta_{1} + \\theta_{2})}$$\n;(2) $$\\frac{z_{1}}{z_{2}} = \\frac{ r_{1}e^{i \\theta_{1}}}{ r_{2}e^{i \\theta_{2}}} = \\frac{r_{1}}{r_{2}}e^{i(\\theta_{1} - \\theta_{2})}$$\n;\n;Let $$z =  re^{i \\theta}$$ and