\left(1-\\frac{3x}{8}+\\frac{3x^2}{128}+\\frac{x^3}{1024}\\right)\\left(1+3x^2\\right);\\\\ = \\left(8-3x+\\frac{3x^2}{16}+\\frac{x^3}{128}\\right)\\left(1+3x^2\\right);\\\\ \\approx 8 - 3x +\\left(\\frac{3}{16}+24\\right)x^2 + \\left(\\frac{1}{128}-9\\right)x^3;\\\\ = 8 - 3x + \\frac{387}{16}x^2-\\frac{1153}{128}x^3\\end{aligned}$$;;(iii);$$\\therefore$$ For expansion in part (ii) to be valid, $$\\left|\\frac{x}{4}\\right| < 1$$ and $$\\left|2x^2\\right| < 1$$.;$$\\begin{aligned} \\left|\\frac{x}{4}\\right| < 1 \\Rightarrow -4 < x <4;\\\\;\\\\ \\left|2x^2\\right| < 1 \\Rightarrow 2x^2 - 1 < 0;\\\\ x^2-\\frac{1}{2} < 0 \\Rightarrow \\left(x-\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}\\right)\\left(x+\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}\\right)<0;\\\\ \\Rightarrow -\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2} < x < \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}\\end{aligned}$$;;$$\\therefore$$ The set of values of $$x = \\left\\{x \\in \\mathbb{R}: -\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2} < x < \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}\\right\\}$$','200704003003'),(1762,'(i) ;$$\\therefore$$ The exact value of $$\\int^{\\frac{2}{3}\\pi}_{0} \\sin^{2}{x} \\space dx$$;$$\\begin{aligned} = \\int^{\\frac{2}{3}\\pi}_{0} \\frac{1-\\cos{2x}}{2} \\space dx \\space (Use \\space \\cos{2x} = 1-2\\sin^{2} x);\\\\ = \\left[\\frac{x}{2} - \\frac{\\sin{2x}}{4}\\right]^{\\frac{2}{3}\\pi}_{0};\\\\ = \\frac{5\\pi}{6} - \\frac{\\sin{\\frac{10\\pi}{3}}}{4};\\\\ = \\frac{5}{6}\\pi + \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{8}\\end{aligned}$$;;$$\\therefore$$ The exact value of $$\\int^{\\frac{5}{3}\\pi}_{0} \\cos^{2}{x} \\space dx$$;$$\\begin{aligned} = \\int^{\\frac{5}{3}\\pi}_{0} (1-\\sin^{2}{x}) \\space dx;\\\\ = \\left[x\\right]^{\\frac{5}{3}\\pi}_{0} - \\frac{5\\pi}{6} - \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{8};\\\\ = \\frac{5\\pi}{3} - \\frac{5\\pi}{6} - \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{8};\\\\ = \\frac{5}{6}\\pi - \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{8}\\end{aligned}$$;;(ii);The shaded region R is bounded by the curve $$y=x^2\\sin{x}$$, the line $$x=\\frac{1}{2}\\pi$$ and the part of the x-axis between 0  and $$\\frac{1}{2}\\pi$$ as shown.;img;;a);$$\\therefore$$ The exact area of R